{"word":"δάκρυμα","slug":"δάκρυμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δάκρυμα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δακρύω'><el>δακρύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that which is wept for, a subject for tears</i>, Orac. <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>that which is wept, a tear</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}